      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/51/3",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اَللَّهِ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهِ : إِذَا عَمِيَ اَلْعَبْدُ فَلاَ رِقَّ عَلَيْهِ وَ اَلْعَبْدُ إِذَا أَجْذَمَ فَلاَ رِقَّ عَلَيْهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3517 - Al-Sakooni narrated from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) from his father, Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), from his forefathers, peace be upon them, who said:\nThe Messenger of Allah (swt), peace be upon him and his family, said: \"If a slave becomes blind, there is no servitude upon him; and if a slave becomes leprous, there is no servitude upon him.\""
        ]
      }
    },
